MAKURDI – The National Association of Women in Agriculture (NAWIA) in Benue State has challenged nine female local government area chairman-elects in the state on the need to empower women economically. NAWIA disclosed this during an agenda-setting lunch in Makurdi on Thursday to honour the incoming female council chairmen in the state. The occasion, which drew women from all parts of the state, was funded by the Development Research and Project Center (DRPC), under the Partnership for Advancing Women in Economic Development (PAWED). -Advertisement- Delivering her welcome address at the event, the NAWIA president, Mrs. Ngizan Chahul, noted that the organisation decided to honour the incoming female chairmen and also brief them on the challenges facing women in the society. She praised NAWIA for being in the forefront of the advocacy for the election of more women in political positions, an initiative that led to the election of nine women as council chairmen, adding that this was the first time in the history of the state that such a large number of women assumed leadership positions in the state.